<h1>Research</h1>

<p>
My research interest is in the field of discrete Mathematics.
I am particularly interested in polyhedral combinatorics, combinatorial
optimization and graph theory.
</p>
<p>
    I am very interested in <a href="mink.php">Minkowski sums of polytopes</a>,
    which I have studied for my PhD thesis. Minkowski sums have
    countless applications, and their combinatorial properties
    have been little studied so far.
</p>
<p>
    My interest in Minkowski sums has led me to looking for counter-examples
    to the Hirsch conjecture. The results of my research are
    <a href=hirsch.php>here</a>.
</p>
<p>
    I am currently working on multicommodity flows.
</p>
<p>
    I am also working on the 3D visibility skeleton, which is a data structure
    encoding visibility information for a set of given scene objects. Roughly
    speaking, the visibility skeleton data structure partitions line space
    into connected components such that the set of line segments in the
    same component are tangent to the same objects.
</p>

